{"ID":270252, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"252\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs251.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs253.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 252<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">he put his hand unto; it was because he and his family obeyed the counsel of the Lord.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">When Egypt was under the superintendence of Joseph<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> it prospered, because he was taught of\n  God;<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> when they oppressed the Israelites,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> destruction came upon them.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> When the children of Israel\n  were chosen with Moses at their head, they were to be a peculiar people,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> among whom God should\n  place His name;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> their motto was: &ldquo;The Lord is our lawgiver; the Lord is our Judge; the Lord is our\n  King; and He shall reign over us.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> While in this state they might truly say, &ldquo;Happy is that people,\n  whose God is the Lord.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> Their government was a theocracy; they had God to make their laws,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and\n  men chosen by Him to administer them;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> He was their God, and they were His people.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> Moses\n  received the word of the Lord from God Himself;<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> he was the mouth of God to Aaron,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> and Aaron\n  taught the people,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> in both civil and ecclesiastical affairs; they were both one, there was no\n  distinction; so will it be when the purposes of God shall be accomplished:<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> when &ldquo;the Lord shall\n  be King over the whole earth&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and &ldquo;Jerusalem His throne.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> &ldquo;The law shall go forth from Zion,\n  and the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Universal Peace to Come from God<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">This is the only thing that can bring about the &ldquo;restitution of all things spoken of by all the holy\n  Prophets since the world was&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span>&mdash;&ldquo;the dispensation of the fullness of times, when God shall gather\n  together all things in one.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> Other attempts to promote universal peace and happiness in the human\n  family have proved abortive; every effort has failed; every plan and design has fallen to the ground;\n  it needs the wisdom of God,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> the intelligence of God,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> and the power of God to accomplish this.\n  The world has had a fair trial for six thousand years; the Lord will try the seventh thousand\n  Himself;<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> &ldquo;He whose right it is,<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> will possess the kingdom,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and reign until He has put all things\n  under His feet;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> iniquity will hide its hoary head,<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> Satan will be bound,<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> and the works of\n  darkness destroyed;<span class=\"footRef\">30<\/span> righteousness will be put to the line, and judgment to the plummet,<span class=\"footRef\">31<\/span> and &ldquo;he\n  that fears the Lord will alone be exalted in that day.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">32<\/span> To bring about this state of things, there must\n  of necessity be great confusion among the nations of the earth; &ldquo;distress of nations with\n  perplexity.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">33<\/span> Am I asked what is the cause of<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106044\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106044)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106044)\">Gen. 22:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106051\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106051)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106051)\">Gen. 26:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111393\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111393)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111393)\">Jacob 4:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106070\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106070)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106070)\">Gen. 41:39-45<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106769\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106769)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106769)\">Ps. 71:17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108698\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108698)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108698)\">John 6:45<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109940\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109940)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109940)\">1 Thes. 4:9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106087\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106087)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106087)\">Ex. 1:13-14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106143\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106143)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106143)\">Ex. 14:26-31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"fo